<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING COMPRESSOR AND CLUTCH TWO CYLINDER RECIPROCATING TYPE - BEFORE 01/01/1993 (R-12) - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - SHAFT SEAL ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1601303" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="8">
        <title>SHAFT SEAL ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The seal can be replaced without compressor removal; however, the system must be discharged.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clutch assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16013j_HL1601302.xml" xrefid="hl1601302">CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using two screwdrivers or similar tools, pry the dust cap from the crankshaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601312">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601312" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601312" filename="../figg16/G1601312.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Prying the Dust Cap From the Crankshaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove capscrews securing the crankshaft seal plate to the crankcase, then remove seal
                    plate and square O-ring seal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601313">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601313" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601313" filename="../figg16/G1601313.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Removing Crankshaft Seal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. O-RING SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SEAL PLATE</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. CRANKSHAFT SEAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a seal puller, remove the crankshaft seal (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601314">Figure 14</hotlnk>). Make sure puller legs are under the lower edge of
                    seal for a secure grip (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601315">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601314" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601314" filename="../figg16/G1601314.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Removing Crankshaft Seal</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1601315" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601315" filename="../figg16/G1601315.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Crankshaft Seal Removed</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SEAL PULLER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. CRANKSHAFT</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Dip seal gland in the type of refrigerant oil used in the system. Remove the carbon ring
                    from the seal gland assembly and set aside. Use a seal gland installing tool to push the lubricated
                    gland assembly onto the shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601316">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601316" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601316" filename="../figg16/G1601316.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Installing Crankshaft Seal</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SEAL INSTALLER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. CRANKSHAFT SEAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Do not touch the lapped surface of the carbon ring. Be sure it is coated with compressor
                            oil.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the carbon ring in the ring retainer so the lapped surface is facing outward. Be
                    sure the notches in the outside edge of the carbon ring engage the dimpled driving lugs in the seal
                    spring adapter (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601317">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601317" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601317" filename="../figg16/G1601317.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Installing Shaft Seal Carbon Ring</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the new O-ring with the type of refrigerant oil used in the system and place
                    it in the groove of the seal plate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the seal plate with uniform clearance around the shaft and install the six
                    capscrews (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601318">Figure 18</hotlnk>). Tighten the capscrews in the proper sequence (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601319">Figure 19</hotlnk>) 5 to 7 ft-lbs. (7 to 9 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601318" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601318" filename="../figg16/G1601318.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 18. Installing the Seal Plate</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1601319" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601319" filename="../figg16/G1601319.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. Crankshaft Seal Plate Capscrew Tightening Sequence</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the dust cover on the crankshaft. The compressor drive clutch will correctly
                    position dust cap when it is installed. Install key in crankshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the clutch assembly. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16013j_HL1601302.xml" xrefid="hl1601302">CLUTCH ASSEMBLY</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
